  "prompt": "What hand drawn anime is out there?",
  "response": "Hand-drawn anime, also known as traditional animation, involves animators drawing each frame by hand. This method was the primary way to create anime before the advent of digital tools. Here are some notable examples of hand-drawn anime:\n\n1. **\"Akira\" (1988)**: Directed by Katsuhiro Otomo and based on his manga, this film is a landmark in anime history. Its detailed hand-drawn animation and dynamic sequences set a high standard for the industry.\n\n2. **\"Spirited Away\" (2001)**: Directed by Hayao Miyazaki at Studio Ghibli. This Academy Award-winning film showcases the meticulous hand-drawn artistry and storytelling that Ghibli is known for.\n\n3. **\"Grave of the Fireflies\" (1988)**: Directed by Isao Takahata. This poignant Studio Ghibli film is renowned for its emotional depth and exquisite hand-drawn animation.\n\n4. **\"Perfect Blue\" (1997)**: Directed by Satoshi Kon. This psychological thriller is praised for its intricate hand-drawn sequences and its exploration of identity and reality.\n\n5. **\"Cowboy Bebop: The Movie\" (2001)**: Directed by Shinichiro Watanabe. Known for its stylish animation and jazz-inspired soundtrack, the film retains the hand-drawn charm of the original TV series.\n\n6. **\"Ghost in the Shell\" (1995)**: Directed by Mamoru Oshii. This cyberpunk classic is celebrated for its detailed hand-drawn animation and philosophical themes.\n\n7. **\"Nausica\u00e4 of the Valley of the Wind\" (1984)**: Directed by Hayao Miyazaki. This early work by Miyazaki is a masterpiece of hand-drawn animation and environmental storytelling.\n\n8. **\"Princess Mononoke\" (1997)**: Also directed by Hayao Miyazaki. This epic fantasy film combines hand-drawn animation with complex characters and moral dilemmas.\n\n9. **\"The Tale of the Princess Kaguya\" (2013)**: Directed by Isao Takahata. This Studio Ghibli film uses a unique watercolor and hand-drawn style to tell its story.\n\n10. **\"Porco Rosso\" (1992)**: Directed by Hayao Miyazaki. This adventurous and whimsical film is another example of Ghibli's hand-drawn excellence.\n\nThese films and series exemplify the artistry and craftsmanship of hand-drawn animation in anime. While many studios have transitioned to digital techniques, the legacy of hand-drawn anime continues to be influential and cherished.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
